prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "Users can browse products through a catalog.",
      "evidence_quote": "users can browse products through a catalog."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Users can view items directly or explore different ways of browsing in the catalog.",
      "evidence_quote": "they can view items directly or explore different ways of browsing."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Users can browse products using an index, either by browsing alphabetically or by category.",
      "evidence_quote": "users can look through products using an index, either by browsing alphabetically or by category."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Users can switch between browsing options depending on their preference.",
      "evidence_quote": "they can switch between these options depending on how they prefer to search."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Once a user finds an interesting product, they can select it to view its details.",
      "evidence_quote": "once they find something interesting, they can select a product to view its details."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Users can go to their basket at any time to review the items they have selected.",
      "evidence_quote": "the user can choose to go to their basket to review the items they have selected."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "From the basket, users can either return to the catalog or move forward to checkout.",
      "evidence_quote": "from there, they can either return to the catalog to continue browsing or move forward to checkout."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "During checkout, users review their selections and proceed with the purchase.",
      "evidence_quote": "during checkout, the user reviews their selections and proceeds with the purchase."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Users can go back to the catalog from the checkout page if they need to make changes before completing the process.",
      "evidence_quote": "if needed, they can still go back to the catalog to make changes before completing the process."
    }
  ]
}

